RIYADH: Islamic Development Bank President Dr. Mohammed Al-Jasser met and discussed cooperation with the ambassador of the Republic of Gabon to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Membourou Guy Ibrahim.
Dr. Al-Jasser underlined the growing and satisfactory cooperation with the Republic of Gabon, stressing the active portfolio of the Islamic Development Bank Group in the country, the bankâ€™s readiness to enhance cooperation in bilateral and regional initiatives, and continuing to deal with the country in priority strategic areas.
For his part, Ambassador Membourou emphasized strengthening cooperation between the Islamic Development Bank Group and the Republic of Gabon, hoping that Gabon would benefit from the scholarship program of the Islamic Development Bank as part of its human capital development efforts.  